# Pre-Push Build Validation

## MANDATORY: Run before every commit & push

Before committing or pushing ANY code changes, you MUST run `npx tsc --noEmit` to catch TypeScript errors. If errors are found, fix them ALL before committing — do not involve the user unless the fix is ambiguous.

## Common Framer Motion pitfall

Cubic-bezier ease arrays in standalone variant objects widen to `number[]`. Always assert the tuple:

```tsx
// BAD — breaks the build
ease: [0.25, 0.46, 0.45, 0.94],

// GOOD
ease: [0.25, 0.46, 0.45, 0.94] as [number, number, number, number],
```

## Workflow

1. Make code changes
2. Run `npx tsc --noEmit`
3. If errors → fix them, re-run step 2
4. Only when step 2 passes with exit code 0 → commit & push
